ABUJA – The Surveyor General of the Federation (SGoF), Surveyor Abuduganiyu Adeyemi Adebomehin, has advocated for the annual Surveying Day Celebration to boost awareness on the importance of surveying and mapping. He also noted that it will help Nigerians to imbibe the culture of using geospatial information in development plans and implementation. Adebomehin, in a statement by his Head, Press and Public Relations, Abu Michael, advocated this at the 17th National Conference of Women In Surveying (WIS) in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State. Biden Signs Order On Cryptocurrency As Its Use Explodes India Logs 4,575 New COVID-19 Cases, 145 Fatalities In 24 Hours He called on the Nigerian Institution of Surveyors (NIS) and the Surveyors Council of Nigeria (SURCON) and other stakeholders to collaborate with the Office of the Surveyor General of the Federation (OSGoF) to initiate the National Surveying Day Celebration. The SGoF said such celebration would stimulate the appropriate reactions from policymakers and political leaders towards promoting the activities of Surveying and Mapping, adding that Surveying associations in developed countries usually celebrate Global Surveyor’s Day every third week of March, to promote the roles of Surveyors. The scope of Surveying and Mapping, according to him, covers much more than transportation, aviation, agriculture, telecommunications, power and energy, disaster management, mining, water resources management, the downstream, health, tourism, the air space, construction and economic activities. He added that the role of the Surveyors has been defined for generations.